      What is a high resolution screen?
      A screen that has a resolution of 1920 x 1080 (a popular resolution often known as 1080p or Full HD), can display 1,080 pixels vertically, and 1,920 pixels horizontally. The higher the number of pixels a screen can show, the sharper and more detailed the image quality.May 24, 2021
